  "narrative_arc": "Chemistry teacher diagnosed with cancer who can't afford treatment on his salary. Gilligan documents the fiscal architecture that drives the plot — the exact gap between a teacher's insurance and cancer treatment costs, the second job at a car wash, the student loan debt, the new baby. Walter doesn't cook meth because he's evil; he cooks meth because the healthcare system is broken.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Walter White is the most famous fictional argument that the American healthcare system creates crime. His dome's Layer 3 (Fiscal) and Layer 4 (Health) gap IS the entire plot. Building his dome with real ACA-era insurance reveals whether his story is still possible.",
